http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Farmer-dies-of-burns/article14013299.ece

A farmer from Mandya died of burns, which he had sustained during Makara Sankranti festivities on January 15, at K.R. Hospital in Mysuru on Wednesday.The deceased has been identified as Harish (30), who was residing in a house near Jayalakshmi Theatre, near Guthalu, here.According to Nagaratna, his wife, Mr. Harish was suffered severe injuries while passing through a wall that was blazing with fire along with his cattle during Makara Sankranti.Mr. Harish had preliminary treatment at the Mandya Institute of Medical Sciences (MIMS) hospital here and later shifted to K.R. Hospital in Mysuru, the Mandya East police said.The Mandya East police have registered a case.